         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Offshore platform installation (OSY) for the MOG project</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="34514800"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="WORKS"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Installation of the Offshore SwitchYard (OSY) Platform for the Modular Offshore Grid (MOG) project including but not limited to: installation, engineering, providing cargobarge, transport to the offshore location and demobilization of installation spread. Main case: installation of jacket and piles by the end of 2018, installation of topside in first half of 2019.</P>
               <P>The final contracting entity may be:</P>
               <P>(i) Elia Asset S.A. and/or Elia System Operator SA; and/or</P>
               <P>(ii) Any company belonging to the Elia group; and/or</P>
               <P>(iii) A new company that will be set up by one of the companies of the Elia Group.</P>
               <P>More information will be given in the call for tender.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="76522000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="76520000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="76521000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="BE"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Offshore Platform Installation: Belgian North Sea.</P>
                  <P>Fabrication Yard: Location unknown.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Scope of work for the Offshore Installation Contractor:</P>
                  <P>— Installation engineering (e.g. rigging, mooring, barge tow ballast, anchor positions, etc.),</P>
                  <P>— Check Detailed Design of the permanent structure interfaces with the installation works (e.g. pad-eyes, upper grillage, clearances, noise mitigation provisions, etc.),</P>
                  <P>— Grillage &amp; seafastening design (all structures),</P>
                  <P>— Obtain (engineering) approval for sail &amp; installation from Marine Warranty Surveyor (prior sail),</P>
                  <P>— Provide cargobarge for seatransport at fabrication yard (hand-over / pick-up at fabrication yard),</P>
                  <P>— Provide rigging at fabrication yard,</P>
                  <P>— Inspection of all installed installation aids prior sail (grillages, seafastening, guides / bumpers, rigging frames, etc.),</P>
                  <P>— Transport of project to offshore location (by tugs, towing cargobarge),</P>
                  <P>— Mobilization installation spread at offshore location (on anchors or DP),</P>
                  <P>— Perform seabed survey at offshore location prior installation of project (confirm level of seabed),</P>
                  <P>— Install pre-designed noise mitigation equipment prior pile driving,</P>
                  <P>— Install, level and weld the project packages (battered jacket max weight 1500 ton, piles max length 100m, topside max weight 2000 ton),</P>
                  <P>— Remove temporary installation provisions on project (rigging frames, guides / bumpers, temporary lift braces),</P>
                  <P>— Re-install project specific items that can’t be done after demobilization installation spread (helideck hatches, fall protection, ladder parts, etc.),</P>
                  <P>— Remove any debris on the platform, repair of damages caused by the Offshore Installation Contractor to permanent structures,</P>
                  <P>— Perform final seabed survey, check for any debris at seabed (and removal),</P>
                  <P>— Demobilization installation spread,</P>
                  <P>— Cleaning of cargo barge,</P>
                  <P>— As-installed engineering package.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <OPTIONS/>
               <OPTIONS_DESCR>
                  <P>If applicable, will be described in the call for tender.</P>
               </OPTIONS_DESCR>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
